Exotel (SDE 2) - Feb-2020 to Feb-2023

Live Call Dashboard

tools used react golang mongo

A dashboard for clients to see the analytics live in a glance.

We developed a React based dashboard with graphs for most important live information and tables/cards for other information. It is powered by a go API service serving analytics from MongoDB, another go service was consuming events from a Kafka cluster where all the services were sending events and either putting it directly in MongoDB for live stats or aggregating it in 5mins chunks for historical stats.

It allowed the account admins to get an idea of what is happening in their contact center at a glance. They could also get more granular and differently categorized data to assess their agent's and team's performance by following cross links which preserved applied date, group and agent filters.

Notification service

tools used javascript golang websockets

A notification service to push notifications to browser

This service connected and maintained websocket connections with browser tabs. On receiving an event it pushed the notification to the relevant user's browser, which was picked up by the frontend code and shown to the user on the website and as a desktop notification.

React integration with PHP

tools used javascript React PHP

Integrated react Single Page App with PHP Multi Page App

The main Exotel dashboard is developed using PHP and jQuery, as several new upcoming projects required sophisticated UI and fast iteration. The deadlines didn't allow for micro-frontend architecture modal to be implemented.

I implemented Live Call Dashboard in react as an SPA and integrated it with PHP backend so that the pages developed in PHP and jQuery continue to function as before and the pages developed in React can be accessed on new routes.

I wrote, maintained, owned, documented and mentored others for:

  • CD pipeline for deploying PHP and React projects together using jenkins AWS-s3 and AWS-EC2
  • Integration code to load react bundle on relevant routes only
  • CSS scoping so the old and new styling don't conflict with each other
  • APIs to pass data between server side PHP and client side React
    • data to be present during page load injected into JS while PHP is forming the response
    • non critical data could be requested by react through API calls

This made future UI development faster and fixed some of the performance issues that old pages faced. Newer pages were available quickly as the UI was loaded with minimal data and further data could be fetched parallelly or when needed reducing server cost and page load times.
